## 5. Roles & Responsibilities
| Role | Responsibility |
|---|---|
| [Security Officer / CISO] | Owns and maintains the register; ensures scoring consistency; reports posture to leadership. |
| Risk Owners | Keep their entries current; drive treatment; confirm residual scores. |
| System / Asset Owners | Provide threat/vulnerability input for systems they own. |

See `../governance/roles-and-responsibilities.md.template`.

## 6. Exceptions
This register records exceptions and accepted risks; the acceptance process itself follows `../governance/exceptions-and-waivers.md.template` and `risk-acceptance.md.template`.

## 7. Compliance, Monitoring & Enforcement
The register is reviewed on the cadence defined in POL-RSK-01 (§11) and at management review (`../governance/management-review.md.template`). Assessors review it as primary evidence of the risk management process. Stale entries (past their Review Date) are flagged by the [Security Officer].

